        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:16PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Harlowton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, along with brief heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Deadmans Basin Reservoir and Shawmut.

Gusty cross winds are expected on US-12 east of Harlowton.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
